        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(memory): unify agent-scoped memory configuration",
        "body": "## What Changes\n\nMemory configuration becomes agent-owned instead of global. `agents.defaults.memory` defines the baseline; `agents.list[].memory` is the per-agent override.\n\n### Before\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"memory\": { \"backend\": \"qmd\", \"qmd\": { /* ... */ } },\n  \"memorySearch\": { \"provider\": \"openai\", /* ... */ },\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": { \"memorySearch\": { /* ... */ } },\n    \"list\": [\n      { \"id\": \"research\", \"memorySearch\": { /* ... */ }, \"dreaming\": { \"enabled\": true } }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### After\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"memory\": {\n        \"backend\": \"builtin\",\n        \"search\": { \"provider\": \"openai\", /* ... */ },\n        \"extensions\": {\n          \"memory-core\": { \"dreaming\": { \"enabled\": false } }\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"list\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"research\",\n        \"memory\": {\n          \"backend\": \"qmd\",\n          \"qmd\": { /* ... */ },\n          \"extensions\": {\n            \"memory-core\": { \"dreaming\": { \"enabled\": true } }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`memory.search.store.path` is removed. Builtin indexes live in the selected agent's database rather than a configurable SQLite sidecar.\n\n### Runtime Behavior\n\n- The resolved agent selects the memory backend, search/index configuration, QMD collections and startup, dreaming, Memory Wiki state, promotion work, context/citations, and the Dreams UI.\n- Defaults apply to every agent; an entry in `agents.list[].memory` overrides that agent only.\n- Dreaming is scheduled only for resolved agents with dreaming enabled. An all-agent opt-out stays opted out; the default-agent fallback is used only when no valid configured agent exists.\n- Gateway and UI requests carry the target agent identity. Unknown gateway agents are rejected rather than falling back to another agent's memory.\n- Dream artifacts are excluded from builtin and QMD indexing, including configured cross-workspace extra paths. Shared-workspace handling is keyed by the physical workspace to avoid cross-agent leakage.\n\n### Doctor And Migration\n\nUse `openclaw doctor --lint` to detect legacy configuration, then `openclaw doctor --fix` to migrate it.\n\n- Top-level `memory` moves to `agents.defaults.memory`; top-level and default `memorySearch` move to `agents.defaults.memory.search`.\n- Per-agent `memorySearch` and `dreaming` move under `agents.list[].memory`, with dreaming becoming `memory.extensions.memory-core.dreaming`.\n- When both shapes are present, doctor fills missing fields from legacy config and keeps explicit agent-scoped values.\n- Legacy `provider: \"auto\"` becomes `\"openai\"`; legacy `memorySearch.store.path` is removed because indexes now use the agent database.\n- Memory Core migrates unscoped dreaming state and legacy dream diaries into agent-scoped state. Memory Wiki migrates its source-sync and import-run state into the agent-scoped store.\n- State migration preserves existing agent entries, archives migrated file sources as `*.migrated`, and warns instead of guessing when a shared workspace cannot be attributed to its resolved default agent.\n\n### Validation\n\n- Focused regression suites cover Memory Core, memory-host SDK, gateway startup/agent validation, and Dreams UI agent selection.\n- `pnpm check:changed` passed in Blacksmith Testbox before the final two-file privacy follow-up; the final retry passed structural checks and typecheck but ended with Testbox exit 255 before reporting a failed lane.\n- Fresh autoreview: no accepted or actionable findings.\n\nAI-assisted; maintainer-reviewed.",
